entries.text: okay tell me about the hardest decision you have ever had to make

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: the hardest decision i have ever had to make well it was when i was sixteen years old and i became a teenage mother i was pregnant at sixteen and i had a lot of pressure from family to give my child up for adoption or to abort and i chose life so that was that was one of the hardest decisions if not the hardest decisions to make as a sixteen year old teenage teenager just whether i wanted to continue to be a kid and a teenager or whether i wanted to embark on raising a life when i was just a child myself so that i think was the hardest decision i had to make

entries.text: i am most proud of where i have come from as a teenage mother being a statistic and actually changing that being on my same i have had my same job for fifteen years now i am really proud of that i have been married for thirteen years i am really proud of that happily married to my best friend and my soulmate nothing is perfect but he is my best friend and i love him and i am also proud of my son being the mother that i am and the son that i have raised i am proud of the job that i have done and i am i really applaud myself for that
